## 1. Big Picture — What is Observability?

Observability = the ability to understand what's happening inside a system by looking at its **external outputs**: logs, traces, and metrics.

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                       Your Application                       │
│                                                              │
│   Logs  ──┐    Traces  ──┐    Metrics  ──┐                  │
└───────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┼────────────────────┘
            │              │              │
            ▼              ▼              ▼
      ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
      │         OTel Collector (Hub)         │
      │  Receives → Processes → Exports      │
      └──────┬──────────┬──────────┬─────────┘
             │          │          │
             ▼          ▼          ▼
         OpenSearch   Jaeger    Prometheus
          (Logs)     (Traces)   (Metrics)
```

* **Why not just `console.log`?** In distributed systems (microservices, K8s), logs from one pod don't tell the full story. You need correlated traces (which services were involved in a request) and centralized log storage (search across all pods/services).

