## 3. OpenTelemetry (OTel) — The Standard

**OpenTelemetry** is a vendor-neutral standard for generating, collecting, and exporting telemetry data (logs, traces, metrics).

| Component | What it does |
|-----------|-------------|
| **OTel SDK** | Library you add to your app to generate telemetry (e.g. Python SDK, Java agent) |
| **OTel Collector** | Standalone binary/container that receives, processes, and exports telemetry |
| **OTLP** | OpenTelemetry Protocol — the wire format (gRPC on port 4317, HTTP on port 4318) |

**Key idea:** Your app sends OTLP → OTel Collector → backends (Jaeger, OpenSearch, Prometheus, etc.). The Collector decouples your app from the backend.

---

## 4. Architecture — How the Pieces Fit

### EC2 (VM-based app)

```
App (e.g. Java with OTel agent)
    │  OTLP (4317/4318)
    ▼
OTel Collector (systemd on same EC2)
    │
    ├── Logs  → Vector (remote) → OpenSearch
    └── Traces → Jaeger (remote, OTLP gRPC 4317)
```

### EKS / Kubernetes

```
App Pod (with OTel SDK or sidecar)
    │  OTLP (4317/4318)
    ▼
OTel Collector Pod (Deployment in same namespace)
    │
    ├── Logs  → Vector (cross-cluster or remote) → OpenSearch
    └── Traces → Jaeger (cross-cluster or remote, OTLP gRPC 4317)
```

### Cross-cloud (EKS → OCI)

```
EKS Cluster                          OCI (OKE) Cluster
┌──────────────┐                    ┌──────────────────────┐
│ App Pod      │                    │ Jaeger Collector     │
│    ↓         │                    │   (OTLP 4317, TLS)  │
│ OTel Coll.   │── traces (TLS) ──→│                      │
│    ↓         │                    │ Jaeger Query (UI)    │
│              │── logs (TLS) ────→ │ Vector → OpenSearch  │
└──────────────┘                    └──────────────────────┘
```

