## 6. Jaeger — Distributed Tracing

### a. Components

| Component | Role | Ports |
|-----------|------|-------|
| **Jaeger Collector** | Receives traces (OTLP, Jaeger, Zipkin) | 4317 (OTLP gRPC), 14250 (Jaeger gRPC), 9411 (Zipkin) |
| **Jaeger Query** | UI + query API | 8443 (HTTPS) or 16686 (HTTP) |
| **Jaeger All-in-One** | Collector + Query + Ingester combined (dev/small) | All above |

### b. Storage Backend

Jaeger stores traces in a backend. Common options:

| Backend | When to use |
|---------|-------------|
| **In-memory** | Dev/testing only (data lost on restart) |
| **OpenSearch / Elasticsearch** | Production; full-text search on traces |
| **Cassandra** | Large scale, write-heavy |
| **Kafka** | Buffer between collector and storage |

Config example (environment vars on Jaeger collector):

```yaml
env:
  - name: SPAN_STORAGE_TYPE
    value: elasticsearch
  - name: ES_SERVER_URLS
    value: https://opensearch-host:9200
  - name: ES_USERNAME
    value: admin
  - name: ES_PASSWORD
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: jaeger-es-secret
        key: password
  - name: ES_INDEX_PREFIX
    value: jaeger
  - name: ES_TLS_ENABLED
    value: "true"
```

### c. TLS

Jaeger collector can require TLS on OTLP:

```
--otlp.grpc.tls.enabled=true
--otlp.grpc.tls.cert=/etc/jaeger-tls/tls.crt
--otlp.grpc.tls.key=/etc/jaeger-tls/tls.key
```

Clients (OTel Collector) must connect with TLS:

```yaml
otlp/jaeger:
  endpoint: <JAEGER_HOST>:4317
  tls:
    insecure: false
    insecure_skip_verify: true   # for self-signed certs or IP-based
```

### d. Kubernetes Manifests (Jaeger)

**Namespace:**
```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
  name: jaeger
```

**ServiceAccounts:**
```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: ServiceAccount
metadata:
  name: jaeger-collector
  namespace: jaeger
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: ServiceAccount
metadata:
  name: jaeger-query
  namespace: jaeger
```

**Services (LoadBalancer for external access):**
