## 11. Cross-Cloud: EKS → OCI (OKE)

When your apps are on **EKS (AWS)** but Jaeger/OpenSearch are on **OCI (OKE)**:

| What | How |
|------|-----|
| **Traces** | EKS OTel Collector exports via `otlp/jaeger` → Jaeger Collector on OKE (LoadBalancer IP or DNS, port 4317, TLS) |
| **Logs** | EKS OTel Collector exports via `otlp/vector` → Vector on OKE → OpenSearch |
| **Network** | OKE services use LoadBalancer (public or private IP). EKS must be able to reach that IP (peering, public internet, VPN). |
| **TLS** | Required for cross-network. Use `insecure_skip_verify: true` for self-signed certs. |
| **DNS** | Create A records (e.g. Route53) pointing to OKE LoadBalancer IPs so config uses hostnames (portable across LB IP changes). |

