## 12. DNS and LoadBalancer Tips

- **Use DNS (e.g. `jaeger.example.com`)** in OTel config instead of raw IPs. When the LB IP changes (e.g. after a CIDR move), update DNS only — no config change.
- **Check DNS from inside the cluster:**
  ```bash
  kubectl run -it --rm dns-check --image=busybox --restart=Never -- nslookup jaeger.example.com
  ```
- **Get LoadBalancer IP:**
  ```bash
  kubectl get svc -n jaeger jaeger-collector -o jsonpath='{.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].ip}'
  ```
- **If DNS doesn't resolve from the cluster:** Use the LB IP directly in the exporter config; fix DNS separately.

