## 13. Troubleshooting Checklist

| Problem | What to check |
|---------|---------------|
| **Logs not reaching OpenSearch** | Check Vector auth (username/password). Check OTel Collector logs for export errors. Verify network connectivity (OTel → Vector → OpenSearch). |
| **Traces not in Jaeger UI** | Check OTel Collector logs for Jaeger export errors. Verify TLS config. Check Jaeger collector logs. Verify Jaeger → OpenSearch connectivity. |
| **OTel Collector not receiving** | Check pod is running. Check Service exists. Check app is sending to correct endpoint (4317 or 4318). |
| **401 Unauthorized** | Wrong password in Vector or Jaeger for OpenSearch auth. |
| **DNS not resolving** | Check A record exists. Check from inside the cluster (`nslookup`). Use LB IP as fallback. |
| **Connection refused / timeout** | Security group / firewall blocking. Wrong port. Service not running. |
| **TLS handshake error** | Missing `insecure_skip_verify: true` for self-signed certs. Or TLS not enabled on one side. |

**Quick debug commands (K8s):**

```bash
# Pod status
kubectl get pods -n observability

# OTel Collector logs
kubectl logs -n observability -l app=otel-collector -f

# Test connectivity from inside cluster
kubectl run -it --rm conn-check --image=curlimages/curl --restart=Never -- \
  curl -vsk --connect-timeout 5 https://<JAEGER_HOST>:4317

# Jaeger collector logs (if on same cluster)
kubectl logs -n jaeger -l app.kubernetes.io/component=collector -f
```

